<item>
            <title>[MVD-3100] RBAC App Visibility</title>
                <link>https://jira.rocketsoftware.com/browse/MVD-3100</link>
                <project id="18400" key="MVD">Zowe (Mainframe Virtual Desktop)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;What it is:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Make a storage place in config dataservice to store an array of pluginID &amp;amp; version which state what plugins a user is able to use&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Make GET /plugins consume that to determine what plugins to return to client. If no user has logged in, it returns from instance scope. If user, then from user scope&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;GET /plugins should cache &amp;amp; update cache, per user. Cache should be refreshed from within 60 minutes if not touched by then&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Documentation:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;We need to provide good defaults for administrators, if they need to do any install-time setup, at all&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;We need to instruct administrators on how to modify the list of plugins&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;At minimum, there needs to be two SAF rules (1. non-admin get only GET access, 2. admins get POST &amp;amp; DELETE)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;At minimum, there needs to be initialization of the JSON files for good defaults&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Things to test:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Determine &amp;amp; define a set of apps that are accessible to one user but not the other&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Config service should contain this data in JSON: that one user has one set in their JSON store, and another user has a different set&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The /plugins API should be returning different lists of apps depending on which user is logged in, versus if there is no user logged in yet at all&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;And, as a result of the 3 points above, one user should see a different list of Apps on the desktop from another user depending on this server-side configuration.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Ex: one set of user(s) are supposed to see the tn3270 app, another set of users are supposed to see the VT app, another set of users are supposed to see neither, and another is supposed to see both&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;What it isn&apos;t:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;steps 4-7 of ticket &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.rocketsoftware.com/browse/MVD-3016&quot; title=&quot;[SPIKE] Research mapping relationships between users and plugins&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MVD-3016&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MVD-3016&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;licensing scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
